FBIS3-17896 "drsov061_b_94027" FBIS-SOV-94-061 Document Type:Daily Report 29 Mar 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Military Issues Air Force Cuts Training Due to Lack of Fuel LD2903121694 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1100 GMT 29 Mar 94 LD2903121694 Moscow Mayak Radio Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Training flights have been considerably reduced at several air-defense units in the Far East, because of a shortage of fuel. The air-defense army headquarters told Interfax that unless fuel supplies are sorted out, fighter-interceptors will soon only be able to take off on an occasional basis and training plans will have to be cancelled altogether.
